Jilin Power Share Co. will pay 183
million yuan ($27.5 million) to buy two wind power operators
from Mengdong Century Concord New Energy Co.  The two wind-energy companies each have 49.5-megawatt wind
farms in Jilin province with a power purchase price of 0.58 yuan
a kilowatt-hour, Jilin Power said today in a filing to
Shenzhenâ€™s stock exchange.  Both companies will be wholly owned by Jilin Power once the
deal is completed, according to the filing.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
